The Chronicle TAKUNDA MAODZA IN ABU DHABI, UAE
President Mnangagwa has shortened his visit to the United Arab Emirates to make sure he is involved directly with the national response by way of relief to victims of cyclone Idai induced floods. <img class="wp-image-441126 size-medium" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Untitled-3-4-360x298.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="298" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Untitled-3-4-360x298.jpg 360w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Untitled-3-4-680x563.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Untitled-3-4.jpg 700w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px" /> destruction caused by the cyclone The cyclone has left 28 people dead and infrastructure destroyed. <img class="wp-image-441129 size-medium" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Untitled-4-3-360x298.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="298" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Untitled-4-3-360x298.jpg 360w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Untitled-4-3-680x563.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Untitled-4-3.jpg 700w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px" /> Dakate river in chipinge The President has also incorporated in his schedule a plea for assistance for the cyclone victims and it is understood he has engaged the UAE Red Crescent to chip in with various forms of support. 